        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_840.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Brace 1863</ref> (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">There is a presentation copy of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_840.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Brace 1863</ref> in the Darwin Library–Down (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5214.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Marginalia</hi></ref> 1: 68).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD discussed the correlation of skin and hair with ‘constitutional peculiarities’ in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 242–5; however, Brace’s book is not mentioned.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 10, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3492.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from George Busk, 1 April 1862</ref>, and letters from E. A. Parkes, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3498.xml" resp="#automat">8 April 1862</ref>, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3521.xml" resp="#automat">28 April 1862</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3627.xml" resp="#automat">29 June 1862</ref>. No copy of the printed memorandum has been found (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Freeman 1977</ref>, pp. 111–12); however, the text is given in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 244–5 n. 48.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> 1: 244 n. 48, CD reported that he had received no returns in response to his memorandum.</note>
